<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0e600dd2-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s9404"><num value="9404">§ 9404.</num><heading> Authorization and appropriation of funds</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated to the Department of Health and Human Services to carry out this chapter—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id0e600dd3-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s9404/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> $750,000,000 for fiscal year 2001;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id0e600dd4-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s9404/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> $1,000,000,000 for fiscal year 2002;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id0e600dd5-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s9404/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> $1,500,000,000 for fiscal year 2003; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id0e600dd6-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s9404/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> such sums as may be necessary for each of the fiscal years 2004 and 2005.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id0e600dd7-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795">(<ref href="/us/pl/106/554/s1/a/1/tVIII/s805">Pub. L. 106–554, § 1(a)(1) [title VIII, § 805]</ref>, <date date="2000-12-21">Dec. 21, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/2763">114 Stat. 2763</ref>, 2763A–82.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
